<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1909-06-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1909-06-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="385" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d385">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 20292/2–4.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President of the United
                                    States</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">President of
                                    Mexico</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">The
                                        White House</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-06-25"><hi rend="italic">June 25,
                                1909</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. President</hi>: I have your courteous
                            note of June 16th,<note n="1" xml:id="d385fn1">Not printed.</note> sent
                            me through Judge Wilfley and thank you sincerely for your kindly
                            attitude.</p>
                        <p>I sincerely hope that in the course of a trip I hope to take in September
                            and October in the Southwest I may have the pleasure of meeting you at
                            El Paso or some convenient station at the border. It would gratify me
                            very much to meet one in the flesh who has done so much to establish
                            order and create prosperity in his own country and in so doing has won
                            the admiration of the entire world.</p>
                        <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Wm. H. Taft.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>